npm i -g heroku  (this will install heroku)

npm uninstall -g heroku-cli (this will unistall heroku-cli which is the older verison)

heroku version / heroku -v  (this will give you heroku version)

heroku login (will show heroku  log in email and password) (email may showed up defaultly, then go to next line input psw:2.M)

heroku create (this will create a new apps in heroku website)

git push heroku master ( this will deploy the code in the git to heroku app we just created)


